    <p>Guid­ing the choice of ther­apy is crit­i­cal for can­cer pa­tients, where treat­ment must be timely and drugs can be costly. It is not easy to bridge the gap from bench to bed­side, so it is par­tic­u­larly grat­i­fy­ing to be able to trans­late our find­ings into clin­i­cal ap­pli­ca­tions that will di­rectly ben­e­fit pa­tients and health­care sys­tems.</p>
    <p>PRO­FES­SOR LIM SOON THYE, deputy med­i­cal di­rec­tor (clin­i­cal) of NCCS and a prin­ci­pal in­ves­ti­ga­tor of the im­munother­apy study.</p>


